fields.description:
Sigma now has Thunderdome and User-level flags for enabling tablet charting. You can flip the switch in Thunderdome, then site admins can enable it per-user in user settings (under Add-on modules).

When a user has it enabled, they'll see on-site messaging asking them to try it out. They can then make it their default if they want. Just make sure that looks and works okay. This issue is *only* for testing the "classic" charting side - if there are any issues on the tablet charting side they should be addressed elsewhere.
fields.summary: #14647 Test Classic/Tablet Charting Switching

comments.body: The testing seems to have open issues in #14647
I don't think they're related to this - this is about the user being able to set their own defaults for which UI they use.

So Jordan.. they have tested and the last comment in redmine by Jeff said he had fixes.
What is the status of this,  what do you need tested further?
What changes have been made further?
I guess what I am asking, is how do we move this one forward and who is kicking the can?

This really should have been a separate redmine ticket from charting itself. For this, they just need to confirm that:

1) The tablet charting flags in Thunderdome and Users > Edit work as expected.
2) Tablet charting is properly "advertised", with links, in legacy charting when user has it enabled (per above)
3) When the user has chosen to make tablet charting their default (per-device), users should be taken to tablet charting when clicking "Clinical Charts" or "+" from the patient's homepage.
Jordan - since this has been put in production, should we close this ticket.
I suppose so. I'm still unclear if any testing was actually done on this, though.
